WINNER of the seventh season of the Nigerian Idol Progress Chukwuyem and first runner-up, Zadok are currently learning the blockchain ecosystem. Binance, one of the sponsors of the music reality show, recently engaged the top two contestants about their experiences.   Audiomack launches Keep The Beat Going     Lady Donli thrills at Alliance Francaise     Monalisa Chinda: My plan to celebrate West African heritage   On his contact with Binance, Progress said, “The competition exposed me to the numerous services of Binance and an exciting financial world in cryptocurrency. I see Binance’s services as one that aids the advancement of the country in terms of meeting up with global standards. I also want to thank Binance for investing in talents.” On his part, Zadok said, Binance also spoke to Zadok about his Nigerian Idol experience. “I felt privileged to be a top performer on Nigerian Idol this season, I had priceless moments. Shoutout to Binance for sponsoring the show – I already use Binance and I look forward to working with the company in the future.”